lvez mall directions from highway 280 driving from highway 280 exit page mill road east towards palo alto turn left on junipero serra turn right on campus drive east turn left on bowdoin st turn left on wilbur way turn right in to the parking structure travel down to visitor parking right lane pay at pay machine station walking to the school of education building from the parking structure 6 enter elevator on north side of parking structure next to pay machine station and go to street level turn right out of the elevator right at the street arguello mall go to stop sign bowdoin and turn left walk down to the end of the street galvez mall cross street continue to walk to walk straight pass meyer library on your right turn right on lasuen mall you will see the clock tower on your left the school of education building also known as cubberley is located at 485 lasuen mall walking to ceras center for educational research at stanford building from the parking structure 6 enter elevator on north side of parking structure next to pay machine station and go to street level turn right out of the elevator right at the street arguello mall go to stop sign bowdoin and turn left walk down to the end of the street galvez mall cross street and look for building with glass front and red accents ceras is located at 520 galvez mall parking information parking information parking is limited on the stanford campus everyone who parks on campus must use parking permits or feed the coin meters until 4 pm coin metered spaces are $1.50 per hour stanford parking and transportation services sells one day parking scratchers you must purchase these to park in a lots at the oval and tressider union parking areas visit the parking and transportation services website for helpful information on parking at stanford admissions apply now application requirements recruitment events financing your degree faq visiting suse contact us student profiles life at stanford admitted student guide about stanford 